The paper deals with the analysis of wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the purview of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of stochastic geometry and interference models also suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) and sectorization, which are topics related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively.
